They're just as important because ultimately you're a product of all your experiences and relationships and that's something that Lady Bird highlights especially well
"but where it finds even more success with that concept, though is through Ladybirds relationship with her mother, played by Laurie Metcalf"
"Gerwig penned the script here as well, and she nails the mother-daughter dynamic"
